WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:08.290
Hi. I'm Dylan Minnette.
and I play Clay Jensen.

2
00:00:08.380 --> 00:00:10.670
I'm Katherine Langford.
and I play Hannah Baker.

3
00:00:10.760 --> 00:00:12.920
I'm Justin Prentice. I play Bryce Walker.

4
00:00:13.010 --> 00:00:15.430
I'm Alisha Boe. I play Jessica Davis.

5
00:00:15.510 --> 00:00:17.970
13 Reasons Why is a fictional series

6
00:00:18.050 --> 00:00:20.470
that tackles tough. real-world issues.

7
00:00:20.560 --> 00:00:22.520
taking a look at sexual assault.

8
00:00:22.600 --> 00:00:25.650
substance abuse. suicide. and more.

9
00:00:25.730 --> 00:00:27.900
By shedding a light
on these difficult topics.

10
00:00:27.980 --> 00:00:30.650
we hope our show can help viewers
start a conversation.

11
00:00:30.730 --> 00:00:33.450
But if you are struggling
with these issues yourself.

12
00:00:33.530 --> 00:00:35.450
this series may not be right for you.

13
00:00:35.530 --> 00:00:37.780
or you may want to watch it
with a trusted adult.

14
00:00:37.870 --> 00:00:40.080
And if you ever feel you need someone
to talk with.

15
00:00:40.160 --> 00:00:41.910
reach out to a parent. a friend.

16
00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:44.250
a school counselor.
or an adult you trust.

17
00:00:44.330 --> 00:00:47.540
call a local helpline.
or go to 13ReasonsWhy.info.

18
00:00:47.630 --> 00:00:49.750
Because the minute you start
talking about it.

19
00:00:50.670 --> 00:00:52.130
it gets easier.

20
00:00:54.000 --> 00:01:00.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

21
00:01:01.890 --> 00:01:04.270
[theme music playing]

22
00:01:21.160 --> 00:01:23.660
["More Than Gravity" playing]

23
00:01:30.340 --> 00:01:33.550
[recording]
Hey. it's Hannah. Hannah Baker.

24
00:01:34.420 --> 00:01:38.680
♪ There's not a simple explanation
For the things that I feel ♪

25
00:01:38.760 --> 00:01:39.800
That's right.

26
00:01:39.890 --> 00:01:43.100
Don't adjust your...
whatever device you're hearing this on.

27
00:01:43.180 --> 00:01:46.480
♪ There's no one word
To tell you why I do the things... ♪

28
00:01:46.560 --> 00:01:49.190
It's me. live and in stereo.

29
00:01:49.270 --> 00:01:51.860
No return engagements. no encore.

30
00:01:51.940 --> 00:01:54.400
and this time. absolutely no requests.

31
00:01:55.940 --> 00:01:57.700
Get a snack. Settle in.

32
00:01:58.110 --> 00:02:00.410
Because I'm about to tell you
the story of my life.

33
00:02:00.490 --> 00:02:05.290
♪ I can't love you
I'm too scared to ♪

34
00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:14.340
♪ It's not a trick that's up my sleeve
It's just the heart inside me ♪

35
00:02:17.470 --> 00:02:20.220
♪ And I spend so much time fighting
The man that I... ♪

36
00:02:20.300 --> 00:02:22.350
-She was so pretty.
-Totally.

37
00:02:26.140 --> 00:02:28.690
-What is it again?
-#NeverForget.

38
00:02:29.600 --> 00:02:31.350
[bell rings]

39
00:02:34.440 --> 00:02:37.940
♪ To think what I can't say out loud ♪

40
00:02:38.030 --> 00:02:39.820
What the hell are you doing?

41
00:02:41.320 --> 00:02:42.280
Nothing. I'm just--

42
00:02:42.870 --> 00:02:44.030
Looking for something?

43
00:02:45.410 --> 00:02:46.870
What would I be looking for?

44
00:02:49.290 --> 00:02:50.210
You tell me.

45
00:02:53.000 --> 00:02:54.590
Do you even know my name?

46
00:02:54.670 --> 00:02:59.510
-[scoffs] 'Course I do. Clay.
-Guys. Second bell.

47
00:03:01.720 --> 00:03:04.640
You're not that innocent. Jensen.
I don't give a shit what she says.

48
00:03:07.100 --> 00:03:10.520
Mr. Foley. let's go. Get to homeroom.

49
00:03:13.440 --> 00:03:14.810
You too. Mr. Jensen.

50
00:03:18.070 --> 00:03:21.910
[woman] So. there are a number of ways
to get help if you need it.

51
00:03:21.990 --> 00:03:23.820
or if a friend does. okay?

52
00:03:23.910 --> 00:03:26.910
And all of this information is
on the board outside of my room

53
00:03:26.990 --> 00:03:28.830
or outside of the main office.

54
00:03:28.910 --> 00:03:30.580
It's on the Liberty High home page.

55
00:03:30.660 --> 00:03:33.000
Ms. Bradley. is it possible
we could be done with all this?

56
00:03:34.080 --> 00:03:35.340
I mean. it's been over a week.

57
00:03:35.420 --> 00:03:37.090
Isn't it healthy to. like. move on?

58
00:03:37.170 --> 00:03:38.380
[disgusted murmurs]

59
00:03:38.460 --> 00:03:39.920
Okay. everyone. thank you.

60
00:03:40.010 --> 00:03:41.880
Seriously. I know. it's tragic.

61
00:03:41.970 --> 00:03:44.050
but I don't want to keep being
reminded all the time.

62
00:03:44.140 --> 00:03:45.470
It's depressing.

63
00:03:45.550 --> 00:03:48.600
We're never done with it. Mr. Pratters.
which is why it's important to know

64
00:03:48.680 --> 00:03:51.770
the signs that someone you care for
might need help.

65
00:03:51.850 --> 00:03:54.810
[voice fades to echo] I mean. are they
withdrawing from friends and family?

66
00:03:54.900 --> 00:03:56.860
Is there a change in their appearance?

67
00:03:57.520 --> 00:03:58.860
Are they having trouble in...

68
00:03:58.940 --> 00:04:01.530
[Mrs. Bradley] The group collaboration
project is worth one-fifth

69
00:04:01.610 --> 00:04:04.950
-of your semester grade total. so--
-[bell rings]

70
00:04:05.740 --> 00:04:08.950
Okay. so. please be committed

71
00:04:09.040 --> 00:04:11.540
and constant and fair to each other.

72
00:04:13.960 --> 00:04:15.040
I like the hair.

73
00:04:16.210 --> 00:04:17.460
The short hair. Um...

74
00:04:17.540 --> 00:04:18.840
I liked the long hair. too.

75
00:04:18.920 --> 00:04:21.710
And. um. I realize this makes me seem
wishy-washy.

76
00:04:21.800 --> 00:04:24.050
and I should have said something
the other night.

77
00:04:24.130 --> 00:04:29.260
and in truth I don't actually like change.
but this change seems cool.

78
00:04:31.850 --> 00:04:32.850
Thanks. Clay.

79
00:04:38.360 --> 00:04:39.400
[Mrs. Bradley] Clay?

80
00:04:40.440 --> 00:04:41.280
Clay.

81
00:04:43.110 --> 00:04:44.280
[clears throat] Clay.

82
00:04:46.160 --> 00:04:47.660
-Yeah. sorry. what?
-[students chuckle]

83
00:04:48.370 --> 00:04:49.870
Are you with us?

84
00:04:50.700 --> 00:04:52.870
Yeah. no. I am. I'm with you.

85
00:04:55.790 --> 00:04:58.500
[Mrs. Bradley] So. between now and then.
observe yourself.

86
00:04:58.580 --> 00:05:00.300
Bring in information.

87
00:05:05.130 --> 00:05:07.640
The students did this on their own.

88
00:05:07.720 --> 00:05:10.010
We thought it just best to leave it.

89
00:05:11.560 --> 00:05:12.850
I see.

90
00:05:19.230 --> 00:05:20.570
I'm sorry. um...

91
00:05:22.190 --> 00:05:23.900
Let me try this again.

92
00:05:25.610 --> 00:05:28.030
You'd think there'd be
a master key or something.

93
00:05:28.110 --> 00:05:30.280
Yeah. there was. once.

94
00:05:38.790 --> 00:05:41.750
[Mrs. Baker] She doesn't have any stickers
or pictures inside.

95
00:05:43.340 --> 00:05:45.260
Why doesn't she have any stickers?

96
00:05:46.010 --> 00:05:48.090
-Honey. it's just a locker.
-No. it's Hannah's locker.

97
00:05:48.180 --> 00:05:49.340
Why is it like that?

98
00:05:49.430 --> 00:05:51.180
Ma'am. I really don't know.

99
00:05:58.140 --> 00:06:00.060
This is everything. then?

100
00:06:00.560 --> 00:06:03.360
Yes. I mean. we can
go through the rest in my office.

101
00:06:03.440 --> 00:06:05.150
That way I can return the textbook.

102
00:06:05.230 --> 00:06:06.860
We just need anything personal.

103
00:06:06.940 --> 00:06:10.110
-The lawyer said bring everything.
-[Mr. Baker] Lawyers say a lot of things.

104
00:06:16.120 --> 00:06:19.330
[girls laughing. chattering outside]

105
00:06:19.420 --> 00:06:21.250
-[camera shutter clicks]
-[door shuts]

106
00:06:21.330 --> 00:06:22.750
Oh. Hey. Clay.

107
00:06:24.090 --> 00:06:24.920
Hey. Tyler.

108
00:06:25.920 --> 00:06:27.590
[distant whistle blowing]

109
00:06:27.670 --> 00:06:28.510
What?

110
00:06:30.550 --> 00:06:31.390
Nothing.

111
00:06:40.940 --> 00:06:42.020
[camera shutter clicks]

112
00:06:42.110 --> 00:06:45.780
[boy] No. no. Mom.
it's a stupid school e-mail.

113
00:06:45.860 --> 00:06:47.360
You do not need to come ho--

114
00:06:47.440 --> 00:06:48.650
Uh. hey. hold on.

115
00:06:48.740 --> 00:06:50.070
What the fuck are you doing?

116
00:06:51.070 --> 00:06:53.410
[Tyler] Nothing. Just yearbook stuff.

117
00:06:53.990 --> 00:06:54.830
Get out. dude.

118
00:07:02.290 --> 00:07:05.630
Hey. sorry. Yeah. I'm fine. I'm fine.

119
00:07:05.710 --> 00:07:07.050
Everything's fine here.

120
00:07:08.050 --> 00:07:09.720
Just stay in Aspen.

121
00:07:11.220 --> 00:07:13.760
Yes. I am sure. Mother. 100 percent sure.

122
00:07:13.850 --> 00:07:15.100
Put Dad on the phone.

123
00:07:21.100 --> 00:07:21.940
Clay.

124
00:07:23.100 --> 00:07:25.190
How are you doing. sweetie?

125
00:07:25.270 --> 00:07:26.820
You've been on my mind.

126
00:07:26.900 --> 00:07:28.150
Hey. Courtney.

127
00:07:29.110 --> 00:07:30.030
I have?

128
00:07:30.110 --> 00:07:33.450
Well. I just feel like we all
need to be there for each other

129
00:07:33.530 --> 00:07:35.490
at a time like this. you know?

130
00:07:36.080 --> 00:07:36.910
Sure.

131
00:07:37.580 --> 00:07:39.000
It's all just so sad.

132
00:07:39.080 --> 00:07:41.750
It just doesn't make sense. right?

133
00:07:41.830 --> 00:07:42.670
No.

134
00:07:43.290 --> 00:07:44.290
But. um...

135
00:07:45.420 --> 00:07:46.960
a lot of things don't make sense.

136
00:07:47.040 --> 00:07:49.260
Exactly. So true.

137
00:07:49.590 --> 00:07:53.220
Some things. you know. just don't
have simple explanations. right?

138
00:07:53.300 --> 00:07:55.220
Right. Yeah.

139
00:07:55.890 --> 00:07:57.470
I'm glad we got to talk.

140
00:07:59.270 --> 00:08:00.100
Bye.

141
00:08:02.600 --> 00:08:03.600
Yeah. good talk.

142
00:08:04.650 --> 00:08:05.980
[boy] Hey. Clay.

143
00:08:07.440 --> 00:08:08.690
You want a ride home?

144
00:08:09.570 --> 00:08:10.530
Yeah. sure.

145
00:08:17.990 --> 00:08:18.990
No bike today?

146
00:08:19.580 --> 00:08:23.660
Uh. no. Mom wanted to drive me.
and. you know. talk about things.

147
00:08:24.750 --> 00:08:25.580
Oh.

148
00:08:26.250 --> 00:08:27.460
[engine starts]

149
00:08:30.090 --> 00:08:31.090
Can I play you a tape?

150
00:08:31.670 --> 00:08:32.670
Yeah. of course.

151
00:08:36.050 --> 00:08:37.550
You're still on the old media. huh?

152
00:08:37.640 --> 00:08:40.350
-Uh. it's so much better.
-["Love Will Tear Us Apart" playing]

153
00:08:41.270 --> 00:08:42.810
Everything was better before.

154
00:08:44.850 --> 00:08:45.900
You said it. son.

155
00:08:56.360 --> 00:08:58.870
♪ You cry out in your sleep ♪

156
00:08:59.410 --> 00:09:02.660
♪ All my failings exposed ♪

157
00:09:02.750 --> 00:09:05.670
♪ And there's a taste in my mouth ♪

158
00:09:05.750 --> 00:09:09.210
♪ As desperation takes hold ♪

159
00:09:09.290 --> 00:09:12.460
♪ Is it something so good ♪

160
00:09:12.550 --> 00:09:16.010
-♪ Just can't function no more ♪
-[song fades]

161
00:09:21.310 --> 00:09:22.310
Like so.

162
00:09:22.850 --> 00:09:24.980
Now. if they ask you if it's real butter.
what do you say?

163
00:09:25.810 --> 00:09:27.560
It's a butter-based product.

164
00:09:27.650 --> 00:09:29.230
And smile when you say it.

165
00:09:29.810 --> 00:09:32.690
I know. terrifying.
But it sells the big lie.

166
00:09:33.650 --> 00:09:35.860
Oh. and. uh. little trade secret:

167
00:09:36.240 --> 00:09:37.910
If they're cute.
only put butter on the top

168
00:09:37.990 --> 00:09:40.530
so they have to come back for more
during the movie.

169
00:09:41.830 --> 00:09:43.160
Okay. uh. why?

170
00:09:43.870 --> 00:09:44.950
So you can chat 'em up.

171
00:09:46.410 --> 00:09:48.290
Oh. chat's not really my thing.

172
00:09:50.130 --> 00:09:50.960
I like it.

173
00:09:52.040 --> 00:09:53.590
I think we're gonna get along.

174
00:09:53.670 --> 00:09:56.470
As long as you remember I started here
three weeks before you.

175
00:09:56.550 --> 00:09:59.430
so I have seniority.
which is why I'm training you.

176
00:09:59.970 --> 00:10:01.800
Which is insane if you think about it.

177
00:10:01.890 --> 00:10:03.760
because I just moved here
two months ago

178
00:10:03.850 --> 00:10:05.600
and I have no idea what I'm doing.

179
00:10:06.560 --> 00:10:07.980
I think it's going well.

180
00:10:11.610 --> 00:10:12.820
Do you like it?

181
00:10:12.900 --> 00:10:13.770
Here?

182
00:10:14.690 --> 00:10:17.990
At the Crestmont?
I find the various smells fascinating.

183
00:10:18.070 --> 00:10:19.780
No. this town.

184
00:10:20.360 --> 00:10:21.450
Oh. right. Uh...

185
00:10:22.450 --> 00:10:24.490
I don't have anything to compare it to.

186
00:10:24.580 --> 00:10:26.120
I've lived here all my life.

187
00:10:26.200 --> 00:10:29.290
It's like asking Han Solo "How is space?"

188
00:10:30.370 --> 00:10:33.540
Wow! You're an actual nerd. aren't you?

189
00:10:34.130 --> 00:10:36.510
I admire that.
There's courage in being a nerd.

190
00:10:36.590 --> 00:10:38.340
[car horn honking]

191
00:10:38.420 --> 00:10:39.840
[song continues]

192
00:10:48.310 --> 00:10:49.140
Catch you later.

193
00:12:03.090 --> 00:12:05.720
[mellow jazz playing]

194
00:12:08.390 --> 00:12:10.310
Dad. where's your radio thing?

195
00:12:11.560 --> 00:12:13.480
"My radio thing"?

196
00:12:13.560 --> 00:12:15.690
That thing you play CDs on

197
00:12:15.770 --> 00:12:18.690
when you're painting
or working in the yard or whatever.

198
00:12:18.770 --> 00:12:19.820
My boom box.

199
00:12:20.610 --> 00:12:21.900
That really what they're called?

200
00:12:21.990 --> 00:12:24.450
They were.
I believe now they're called obsolete.

201
00:12:25.280 --> 00:12:26.490
Uh. yeah. it's in the workshop.

202
00:12:27.240 --> 00:12:28.280
It plays tapes. right?

203
00:12:28.370 --> 00:12:29.870
It does. last I checked.

204
00:12:32.870 --> 00:12:34.330
How were things at school today?

205
00:12:37.080 --> 00:12:40.050
Same. Everyone's still acting weird.

206
00:12:41.670 --> 00:12:42.510
And you?

207
00:12:43.510 --> 00:12:44.510
Um...

208
00:12:46.840 --> 00:12:47.890
How are you doing?

209
00:12:49.720 --> 00:12:52.140
Me? I'm... fine.

210
00:12:53.020 --> 00:12:53.850
I'm good.

211
00:12:58.230 --> 00:13:00.770
So. can I-- I can use the boom box?

212
00:13:02.070 --> 00:13:03.490
Yes. of course. The boom box.

213
00:13:03.570 --> 00:13:04.400
Go.

214
00:13:05.030 --> 00:13:07.200
But... keep in touch.

215
00:13:07.780 --> 00:13:08.620
Okay?

216
00:13:09.910 --> 00:13:10.950
Sure thing. Dad.

217
00:13:28.300 --> 00:13:29.970
Hey. it's Hannah.

218
00:13:30.800 --> 00:13:31.810
Hannah Baker.

219
00:13:33.100 --> 00:13:33.930
Holy shit.

220
00:13:34.020 --> 00:13:37.810
Don't adjust your...
whatever device you're hearing this on.

221
00:13:39.100 --> 00:13:42.690
It's me. live and in stereo.

222
00:13:44.490 --> 00:13:47.490
No return engagements. no encore.

223
00:13:47.570 --> 00:13:50.200
and this time. absolutely no requests.

224
00:13:51.410 --> 00:13:53.120
Get a snack. Settle in.

225
00:13:54.040 --> 00:13:56.660
Because I'm about to tell you
the story of my life.

226
00:13:58.000 --> 00:14:00.580
More specifically. why my life ended.

227
00:14:01.920 --> 00:14:03.920
And if you're listening to this tape...

228
00:14:04.670 --> 00:14:06.300
you're one of the reasons why.

229
00:14:08.180 --> 00:14:10.430
I'm not saying which tape
brings you into the story.

230
00:14:10.800 --> 00:14:13.760
But fear not. if you received
this lovely little box.

231
00:14:13.850 --> 00:14:15.470
your name will pop up.

232
00:14:15.560 --> 00:14:16.520
I promise.

233
00:14:17.350 --> 00:14:20.230
Anyway. the rules here are pretty simple.

234
00:14:20.650 --> 00:14:22.310
-There are only two.
-Whatcha doing?

235
00:14:22.400 --> 00:14:23.980
-Jesus!
-Sorry.

236
00:14:24.440 --> 00:14:26.320
What have we said
about helicopter parenting?

237
00:14:26.400 --> 00:14:27.650
I didn't mean to scare you.

238
00:14:27.740 --> 00:14:30.450
You were just lost in--
what is that you're listening to?

239
00:14:30.530 --> 00:14:33.910
It's. uh... it's nothing.
It's for history class.

240
00:14:35.040 --> 00:14:36.450
-Cassettes are history now?
-Mm-hm.

241
00:14:36.540 --> 00:14:37.910
Hm! Of course they are.

242
00:14:38.000 --> 00:14:39.000
Can I listen?

243
00:14:39.080 --> 00:14:40.830
No. uh. it's dumb.

244
00:14:40.920 --> 00:14:42.920
I'm gonna head up to my room. Homework.

245
00:14:47.130 --> 00:14:49.130
Clay. school emailed again today.

246
00:14:50.760 --> 00:14:53.260
Which explains why Dad
showed interest in my life.

247
00:14:53.350 --> 00:14:55.180
You two are dangerous when you coordinate.

248
00:14:55.260 --> 00:14:56.810
You know I hate being the kind of parent

249
00:14:56.890 --> 00:14:59.520
who asks if you want
to talk about anything. but...

250
00:15:00.020 --> 00:15:01.560
if you want to talk about anything...

251
00:15:02.480 --> 00:15:03.940
I didn't really know her. Mom.

252
00:15:04.980 --> 00:15:06.730
Didn't you two work together
at the Crestmont?

253
00:15:07.230 --> 00:15:11.110
-Yeah. for a little while--
-But you didn't know her very well?

254
00:15:11.700 --> 00:15:12.780
Not really.

255
00:15:14.410 --> 00:15:15.780
I need to get to work--

256
00:15:15.870 --> 00:15:17.870
-Shit!
-Language.

257
00:15:17.950 --> 00:15:20.960
I'm sorry. I gotta... I gotta go work.

258
00:15:21.040 --> 00:15:23.500
This thing is due in two days.
so I gotta go.

259
00:15:23.960 --> 00:15:25.000
Clay.

260
00:15:25.750 --> 00:15:26.630
Slow down. hon.

261
00:15:27.630 --> 00:15:28.630
It's just homework.

262
00:15:30.050 --> 00:15:32.130
Yeah. Thanks. Mom.

263
00:15:43.980 --> 00:15:44.980
What the hell?

264
00:15:47.570 --> 00:15:48.610
[grunts]

265
00:16:01.250 --> 00:16:02.080
Shit.

266
00:16:03.120 --> 00:16:04.080
[sighs]

267
00:16:14.260 --> 00:16:15.680
I have to go to Tony's.

268
00:16:16.050 --> 00:16:18.430
Hold on. Tony's? Now?

269
00:16:19.520 --> 00:16:22.060
He needs one of the tapes.
We're working together.

270
00:16:22.140 --> 00:16:23.600
Dinner's in a half hour.

271
00:16:23.690 --> 00:16:25.350
Make me a plate for later?

272
00:16:25.940 --> 00:16:28.440
Text me if you're gonna be later
than really late.

273
00:16:28.770 --> 00:16:30.820
-I will. Bye.
-Bye.

274
00:16:47.750 --> 00:16:49.550
[children chattering]

275
00:17:00.640 --> 00:17:01.600
[horn honking]

276
00:17:15.450 --> 00:17:16.660
Hand me the screwdriver.

277
00:17:18.490 --> 00:17:19.320
Okay.

278
00:17:23.910 --> 00:17:25.330
-Hey. Tony.
-Hey. Clay.

279
00:17:26.040 --> 00:17:28.380
-Something wrong with her?
-Nothing wrong yet.

280
00:17:28.460 --> 00:17:30.170
It's called taking care of things.

281
00:17:31.500 --> 00:17:34.840
-Dad. you remember Clay.
-Yeah. sure.

282
00:17:35.380 --> 00:17:36.380
How you doing. Clay?

283
00:17:37.010 --> 00:17:38.340
I'm well. thank you.

284
00:17:38.430 --> 00:17:39.640
So. Clay. what's up?

285
00:17:40.180 --> 00:17:41.930
Nothing. I was. uh...

286
00:17:42.010 --> 00:17:43.350
I was out for a ride.

287
00:17:43.430 --> 00:17:44.810
On the other side of town?

288
00:17:46.810 --> 00:17:48.650
That should do it. Start her up.

289
00:17:48.730 --> 00:17:50.690
-Hand me the rag.
-I'll do it.

290
00:17:56.570 --> 00:17:58.780
If we got the timing right. we'll hear it.

291
00:17:59.450 --> 00:18:00.740
Okay. flip the ignition.

292
00:18:02.280 --> 00:18:04.870
[engine turning over]

293
00:18:04.950 --> 00:18:06.500
[engine revs]

294
00:18:09.040 --> 00:18:11.590
You hear that? That's how it should sound.

295
00:18:11.670 --> 00:18:14.510
-That sounds different?
-Yeah. it's different. Are you deaf?

296
00:18:14.590 --> 00:18:17.170
-[Tony] Sounds the same as before.
-Then you are deaf.

297
00:18:17.260 --> 00:18:19.970
-That's so much smoother. Night and day.
-[Tony responds indistinctly]

298
00:18:20.050 --> 00:18:22.550
[Tony's dad] I don't think so.
I know. and you should too.

299
00:18:22.640 --> 00:18:24.430
That's why I'm showing you this.

300
00:18:24.520 --> 00:18:25.560
Okay. shut her off.

301
00:18:27.060 --> 00:18:27.940
[engine shuts off]

302
00:18:31.560 --> 00:18:32.980
I should get out of here.

303
00:18:33.070 --> 00:18:35.230
-Sure you don't want to stay for dinner?
-No. thanks.

304
00:18:35.320 --> 00:18:36.650
My mom's making pork chops.

305
00:18:36.740 --> 00:18:39.610
If I'm not home soon.
she'll call the cops or something.

306
00:18:39.700 --> 00:18:41.370
They emailed all the parents again.

307
00:18:41.450 --> 00:18:43.530
-Oh. I know.
-[Tony's dad] She leave a note?

308
00:18:44.410 --> 00:18:45.740
Girl who killed herself?

309
00:18:47.160 --> 00:18:48.000
Uh...

310
00:18:48.580 --> 00:18:49.580
I don't know.

311
00:18:50.710 --> 00:18:52.170
[speaks low in Spanish]

312
00:18:53.000 --> 00:18:54.210
Well. you listen to me.

313
00:18:54.290 --> 00:18:57.300
You ever do that to your mother.
I will kill you. you understand?

314
00:18:58.420 --> 00:18:59.930
I'll kill you dead.

315
00:19:00.010 --> 00:19:01.010
Clean this shit up.

316
00:19:03.550 --> 00:19:05.850
No sense of irony in that comment.

317
00:19:05.930 --> 00:19:07.350
None. He's. uh...

318
00:19:07.430 --> 00:19:08.480
He's a simple man.

319
00:19:08.560 --> 00:19:09.390
Yep.

320
00:19:10.390 --> 00:19:11.650
I'll see you later.

321
00:19:11.730 --> 00:19:13.730
Clay. I think you got something
that belongs to me.

322
00:19:16.320 --> 00:19:17.150
I do?

323
00:19:19.360 --> 00:19:20.400
My keys.

324
00:19:21.110 --> 00:19:22.570
Oh. yeah. right. Here.

325
00:19:23.490 --> 00:19:24.580
I'll see you later.

326
00:19:36.800 --> 00:19:38.840
[Hannah]
The rules here are pretty simple.

327
00:19:38.920 --> 00:19:40.010
There are only two.

328
00:19:41.050 --> 00:19:43.050
Rule number one: you listen.

329
00:19:43.840 --> 00:19:46.050
Number two: you pass it on.

330
00:19:46.850 --> 00:19:49.270
Hopefully. neither one will be easy.

331
00:19:49.350 --> 00:19:52.520
It's not supposed to be easy.
or I would have emailed you an MP3.

332
00:19:52.600 --> 00:19:55.310
When you're done listening
to all 13 sides.

333
00:19:55.400 --> 00:19:58.030
because there are 13 sides
to every story...

334
00:19:58.820 --> 00:20:00.860
rewind the tapes.
put them back in the box.

335
00:20:00.940 --> 00:20:02.950
and pass them on to the next person.

336
00:20:03.030 --> 00:20:04.450
Why the hell am I on this?

337
00:20:04.820 --> 00:20:07.950
Oh. and the box of tapes
should have included a map.

338
00:20:08.870 --> 00:20:11.870
I'll be mentioning several spots
around our beloved city.

339
00:20:12.370 --> 00:20:13.960
I can't force you to visit them.

340
00:20:14.040 --> 00:20:17.750
but if you'd like a little more insight.
head for the stars.

341
00:20:19.300 --> 00:20:22.510
Or. you know. just throw the map away
and I'll never know...

342
00:20:23.880 --> 00:20:24.930
or will I?

343
00:20:27.760 --> 00:20:30.560
You see. in case you're tempted
to break the rules.

344
00:20:30.640 --> 00:20:33.560
understand I did make a copy
of these tapes.

345
00:20:33.640 --> 00:20:35.650
and I left them with a trusted individual

346
00:20:35.730 --> 00:20:38.730
who. if this package doesn't
make it through all of you.

347
00:20:38.820 --> 00:20:41.240
will release those copies
in a very public manner.

348
00:20:42.110 --> 00:20:44.450
This was not
a spur of the moment decision.

349
00:20:44.530 --> 00:20:46.450
Do not take me for granted.

350
00:20:46.910 --> 00:20:47.950
Not again.

351
00:20:48.030 --> 00:20:49.030
I never did!

352
00:20:50.490 --> 00:20:52.290
-[car horn honking]
-Whoa!

353
00:20:52.370 --> 00:20:54.250
-[honking]
-[tires squeal]

354
00:20:55.960 --> 00:20:57.080
[tape player clatters]

355
00:20:58.290 --> 00:21:00.340
[tires squealing away]

356
00:21:01.880 --> 00:21:03.300
[grunts]

357
00:21:04.720 --> 00:21:06.010
[coughs]

358
00:21:10.470 --> 00:21:11.970
[panting]

359
00:21:16.140 --> 00:21:16.980
[groans softly]

360
00:21:19.190 --> 00:21:20.400
Oh. shit.

361
00:21:34.370 --> 00:21:35.210
[grunts]

362
00:21:55.390 --> 00:21:56.640
[Hannah] Do what I say.

363
00:21:57.310 --> 00:21:59.020
Not more. not less.

364
00:22:01.770 --> 00:22:02.980
You're being watched.

365
00:22:17.410 --> 00:22:18.460
Everything okay?

366
00:22:18.540 --> 00:22:20.000
Yeah. No. I just forgot something.

367
00:22:20.080 --> 00:22:21.340
Clay. your forehead!

368
00:22:21.420 --> 00:22:22.670
What? It's nothing.

369
00:22:22.750 --> 00:22:24.380
Did you fall off your bike?

370
00:22:24.460 --> 00:22:27.090
Low-hanging branch.
I went through the woods. It was dark.

371
00:22:27.170 --> 00:22:28.380
I'll get the first aid kit.

372
00:22:28.470 --> 00:22:30.300
I don't need first aid.

373
00:22:30.390 --> 00:22:32.390
You are bleeding. You need ointment.

374
00:22:32.470 --> 00:22:34.060
Mom. please don't say "ointment."

375
00:22:37.230 --> 00:22:38.440
I'm fine. really.

376
00:22:38.520 --> 00:22:41.190
-What happened?
-I told you. bike. branch. skin.

377
00:22:41.270 --> 00:22:42.360
That's all?

378
00:22:42.440 --> 00:22:44.150
Mom. I tell you everything about my life

379
00:22:44.230 --> 00:22:46.230
because it is so fascinating.
I promise.

380
00:22:46.320 --> 00:22:48.400
I'll clean it up. I have to go.
Tony's waiting.

381
00:22:48.490 --> 00:22:49.320
Ah-ah.

382
00:22:53.030 --> 00:22:54.240
Your helmet. please.

383
00:23:09.930 --> 00:23:11.260
[Hannah] Love the helmet.

384
00:23:12.470 --> 00:23:13.510
It's adorable.

385
00:23:14.220 --> 00:23:17.640
You mean "adorable" in a helpless
baby animal sort of way. I'm guessing.

386
00:23:17.720 --> 00:23:19.480
Aren't you afraid of helmet hair?

387
00:23:19.560 --> 00:23:22.190
My hair does the same thing
no matter what. just sits there.

388
00:23:23.270 --> 00:23:24.730
You just need some product.

389
00:23:24.820 --> 00:23:27.110
A little effort to style it.
blow-dry it in the morning.

390
00:23:27.190 --> 00:23:29.150
And sacrifice my masculinity?

391
00:23:29.240 --> 00:23:31.070
That ship has sailed. don't you think?

392
00:23:32.610 --> 00:23:34.990
Forgive me for wanting to keep
my brains in my head.

393
00:23:35.740 --> 00:23:38.370
Instead of. say. some other regions.
like most boys?

394
00:23:39.910 --> 00:23:42.330
Come on. Helmet.
you've got bathrooms to clean.

395
00:23:42.420 --> 00:23:44.920
-You mean "we've got."
-Mm. I don't. actually.

396
00:23:45.630 --> 00:23:48.380
Oh. uh. party at my house
tomorrow night.

397
00:23:48.460 --> 00:23:51.420
You're invited. It's mandatory.
Don't bring the helmet.

398
00:23:54.510 --> 00:23:56.600
Cool. Where. uh... where do you live?

399
00:23:57.470 --> 00:24:00.730
[Hannah] Put your finger on "C."
your other finger on "4."

400
00:24:01.640 --> 00:24:04.980
Bring them together.
That's our first red star.

401
00:24:05.900 --> 00:24:06.770
I know. right?

402
00:24:06.860 --> 00:24:09.990
A map. Old school. again.

403
00:24:10.070 --> 00:24:11.400
No Google Maps.

404
00:24:11.490 --> 00:24:15.910
no app. no chance for the interwebs
to make everything worse. like it does.

405
00:24:30.380 --> 00:24:31.970
[engine revs]

406
00:25:00.660 --> 00:25:02.370
[engine revs. tires squeal]

407
00:25:10.800 --> 00:25:13.970
[Hannah] You've arrived at
my first house in this shitty town...

408
00:25:15.470 --> 00:25:18.180
where I threw my first and only party...

409
00:25:19.760 --> 00:25:21.640
and where I met Justin Foley...

410
00:25:22.430 --> 00:25:24.230
the subject of our first tape.

411
00:25:24.310 --> 00:25:26.650
[rock music plays indistinctly]

412
00:25:28.650 --> 00:25:29.940
It was just a party.

413
00:25:30.980 --> 00:25:33.860
I didn't know it was
the beginning of the end.

414
00:25:33.940 --> 00:25:36.400
-[music continues]
-[overlapping chatter]

415
00:25:39.620 --> 00:25:43.870
Justin. you were in love
with my friend Kat. My only friend.

416
00:25:43.950 --> 00:25:45.960
He came! Clay's here!

417
00:25:46.040 --> 00:25:48.670
-[chuckles]
-I win! You owe me five dollars.

418
00:25:48.750 --> 00:25:49.580
Oh. my God.

419
00:25:49.670 --> 00:25:51.500
-You bet on me?
-Against you.

420
00:25:51.590 --> 00:25:56.010
Last party I saw Clay at...
mm. my birthday. fourth grade.

421
00:25:56.720 --> 00:25:58.840
-I still remember that clown.
-Mm!

422
00:25:58.930 --> 00:26:00.760
Oh. my God. He was a heroin addict.

423
00:26:00.850 --> 00:26:04.980
My mother the social worker
hired a recovering heroin addict.

424
00:26:05.060 --> 00:26:06.480
He had the shakes.

425
00:26:06.890 --> 00:26:09.810
Okay. uh. drinks. Come on. Excuse me.

426
00:26:10.440 --> 00:26:12.650
-I just thought he was nervous.
-[both chuckle]

427
00:26:12.730 --> 00:26:13.730
-Hey.
-Hi. Kat.

428
00:26:15.070 --> 00:26:17.530
This is quite a turnout.
People are happy to see you go.

429
00:26:17.610 --> 00:26:20.820
I really just threw it so Hannah
could finally meet some people

430
00:26:20.910 --> 00:26:23.120
before I depart this realm.

431
00:26:23.200 --> 00:26:24.540
I met Helmet.

432
00:26:24.620 --> 00:26:26.450
Clay doesn't count. You met him at work.

433
00:26:26.540 --> 00:26:29.330
-I feel like that should count.
-Of course you do.

434
00:26:29.420 --> 00:26:32.750
Okay. refills. Clay. what is your drink?

435
00:26:32.840 --> 00:26:34.000
Uh. Sprite.

436
00:26:34.090 --> 00:26:35.920
Oh. my God. you are priceless.

437
00:26:36.010 --> 00:26:38.220
You are a gem. You'll have a beer.

438
00:26:39.300 --> 00:26:40.720
Sure. I like beer.

439
00:26:40.800 --> 00:26:42.600
-[Tyler] Kat.
-Oh. Picture.

440
00:26:43.930 --> 00:26:45.020
[shutter clicks]

441
00:26:48.310 --> 00:26:50.520
Stop having so much fun. Clay.

442
00:26:51.100 --> 00:26:52.690
I'm having fun. totally.

443
00:26:53.190 --> 00:26:54.110
Woot!

444
00:26:56.740 --> 00:26:58.030
You're too buttoned up.

445
00:27:00.950 --> 00:27:02.240
[laughing]

446
00:27:04.660 --> 00:27:05.490
Hey there.

447
00:27:06.240 --> 00:27:07.080
Hey.

448
00:27:07.620 --> 00:27:11.000
You're. um. you're the new girl.

449
00:27:11.580 --> 00:27:12.830
Apparently.

450
00:27:12.920 --> 00:27:15.000
Uh. I like your laugh.

451
00:27:15.090 --> 00:27:16.170
Thanks.

452
00:27:16.250 --> 00:27:18.670
I like your understated sense of fashion.

453
00:27:19.260 --> 00:27:21.380
[chuckles] Thanks.

454
00:27:21.470 --> 00:27:22.340
[Kat] Bryce.

455
00:27:22.970 --> 00:27:25.560
Better go hit the keg and catch up.
You're an hour behind.

456
00:27:27.720 --> 00:27:29.430
I'll see you later... I hope.

457
00:27:29.520 --> 00:27:30.600
See you.

458
00:27:32.730 --> 00:27:35.980
Oh. God. no. Solid no. Hannah.

459
00:27:36.070 --> 00:27:38.280
He is. like. frat boy Darth Vader.

460
00:27:38.360 --> 00:27:39.650
He didn't seem that bad.

461
00:27:40.400 --> 00:27:41.400
I was being kind.

462
00:27:41.490 --> 00:27:42.740
She kind of was.

463
00:27:45.620 --> 00:27:46.870
I think I want a beer too.

464
00:27:48.290 --> 00:27:50.290
Okay. then. Princess Leia.

465
00:27:51.540 --> 00:27:53.170
Oh. my God. you're both nerds.

466
00:27:53.670 --> 00:27:54.790
Have fun.

467
00:28:00.170 --> 00:28:01.090
Are you gonna tell her?

468
00:28:02.590 --> 00:28:03.430
Tell her what?

469
00:28:03.510 --> 00:28:06.430
Oh. please. I've known you
this entire century.

470
00:28:07.510 --> 00:28:09.140
Well. give me a break.

471
00:28:09.220 --> 00:28:10.480
I'm not good with the...

472
00:28:10.930 --> 00:28:13.900
you know.
and the gay rumors only recently subsided.

473
00:28:13.980 --> 00:28:16.400
Mmm. So the stakes are high for you.

474
00:28:18.230 --> 00:28:20.650
It's like. around her.
I can be different. you know?

475
00:28:20.740 --> 00:28:22.570
I'm the new and improved Clay Jensen:

476
00:28:22.650 --> 00:28:26.070
high school sophomore.
archaeologist-slash-adventurer.

477
00:28:27.450 --> 00:28:31.330
Clay. sweets. you're a prize.

478
00:28:31.410 --> 00:28:36.710
But from my limited observation.
she has terrible taste in guys.

479
00:28:39.090 --> 00:28:41.460
You won't say anything to her?

480
00:28:42.970 --> 00:28:43.970
Only if it comes up.

481
00:28:44.430 --> 00:28:45.590
Kat!

482
00:28:46.390 --> 00:28:47.680
[cell phone vibrating]

483
00:28:56.230 --> 00:28:57.060
[phone clicks]

484
00:29:09.700 --> 00:29:11.330
-Shit!
-Watch it!

485
00:29:13.160 --> 00:29:17.330
[laughing. yelling]

486
00:29:17.420 --> 00:29:19.040
No...

487
00:29:19.130 --> 00:29:20.210
[Kat] Meet the boys.

488
00:29:20.300 --> 00:29:24.220
Justin Foley is mine.
and Zach Dempsey for you.

489
00:29:24.630 --> 00:29:26.630
Zach Dempsey? Really?

490
00:29:26.720 --> 00:29:28.390
What? Zach's sweet?

491
00:29:29.470 --> 00:29:30.930
I can't see!

492
00:29:31.010 --> 00:29:31.850
Not the mane!

493
00:29:32.640 --> 00:29:35.060
Okay. yeah. he's kind of dumb.

494
00:29:35.140 --> 00:29:38.060
but he's the sweet kind of dumb.
which is the best kind.

495
00:29:41.400 --> 00:29:42.650
Yes.

496
00:29:42.730 --> 00:29:46.070
Liberty High's star athletes.
ladies and gentlemen.

497
00:29:46.150 --> 00:29:47.950
So impressive.

498
00:29:48.030 --> 00:29:50.910
Sorry. boys. Can't have you
in Hannah's house soaking wet.

499
00:29:50.990 --> 00:29:52.410
Seriously?

500
00:29:52.490 --> 00:29:54.080
Oh. my God. look at yourselves.

501
00:29:55.660 --> 00:29:56.750
Better?

502
00:29:56.830 --> 00:30:00.790
Improvement. for sure.
but sorry. it's still a no-go.

503
00:30:00.880 --> 00:30:02.300
Come on! It's not a party without us.

504
00:30:02.380 --> 00:30:03.550
[Kat] We'll take our chances.

505
00:30:03.630 --> 00:30:04.920
Go dry off.

506
00:30:05.010 --> 00:30:06.550
Your loss. milady.

507
00:30:07.130 --> 00:30:09.010
Idiots. I can't even...

508
00:30:09.260 --> 00:30:10.510
But they're sweet idiots.

509
00:30:17.100 --> 00:30:19.940
[Hannah] So. you see.
that's where the trouble began.

510
00:30:20.020 --> 00:30:21.360
That smile.

511
00:30:23.780 --> 00:30:25.400
That damned smile.

512
00:30:29.610 --> 00:30:32.450
The one and only Kat moved away
before the start of school.

513
00:30:34.370 --> 00:30:37.290
She was the kind of friend
that couldn't be replaced.

514
00:30:37.370 --> 00:30:40.290
even by falling in love
with the boy she left behind.

515
00:30:42.250 --> 00:30:43.090
[Justin] Hey.

516
00:30:45.710 --> 00:30:47.470
-Hannah. right?
-Right.

517
00:30:47.550 --> 00:30:49.550
Justin. Foley.

518
00:30:49.630 --> 00:30:51.720
I saw you at the party the other night.

519
00:30:51.800 --> 00:30:53.430
Yeah. I saw you too.

520
00:30:54.930 --> 00:30:55.930
You're drier now.

521
00:30:56.640 --> 00:30:58.690
Yeah. well. we went home and changed.

522
00:30:59.520 --> 00:31:00.520
Was it profound?

523
00:31:01.310 --> 00:31:02.150
Huh?

524
00:31:02.230 --> 00:31:03.060
Your change.

525
00:31:03.650 --> 00:31:05.610
Oh. yeah. yeah. yeah. Totally.

526
00:31:07.940 --> 00:31:09.450
So. uh...

527
