-Do you know any of them?

665
00:37:55.100 --> 00:37:56.640
[cell phone vibrating]

666
00:37:56.730 --> 00:37:57.900
More homework?

667
00:37:57.980 --> 00:37:59.690
We're just working on this math problem.

668
00:38:00.940 --> 00:38:02.070
Hello. Justin.

669
00:38:02.150 --> 00:38:03.780
Hannah's doing her homework.

670
00:38:04.530 --> 00:38:06.110
[Justin] Oh. hi. Mrs. Baker.

671
00:38:06.200 --> 00:38:08.360
Yeah. she was totally just
helping me with it.

672
00:38:08.450 --> 00:38:11.080
Oh. really? What are you working on?

673
00:38:11.160 --> 00:38:12.580
Uh. math.

674
00:38:12.660 --> 00:38:15.080
Math. Oh.

675
00:38:16.160 --> 00:38:17.080
All right. then.

676
00:38:20.920 --> 00:38:22.380
Let me know if you need my help.

677
00:38:37.600 --> 00:38:40.440
So. you needed help with a math problem?

678
00:38:41.400 --> 00:38:43.650
No. I just said that to get you alone
on the phone.

679
00:38:43.730 --> 00:38:45.690
Because I've got homework of my own.

680
00:38:45.780 --> 00:38:48.320
and I can't just talk on the phone
all afternoon.

681
00:38:48.400 --> 00:38:50.700
Okay. I can call you back.

682
00:38:50.780 --> 00:38:51.620
No! I--

683
00:38:52.660 --> 00:38:57.580
I mean. uh. what problem
were you having trouble with?

684
00:38:58.080 --> 00:39:00.880
The one about the. uh... trains?

685
00:39:01.790 --> 00:39:02.840
The trains?

686
00:39:03.840 --> 00:39:07.760
Two trains leave at different times.
but when do they meet?

687
00:39:09.590 --> 00:39:10.970
Oh! [chuckles]

688
00:39:11.050 --> 00:39:12.890
I get it. Um...

689
00:39:12.970 --> 00:39:16.430
Train "A" is leaving my house
in a few minutes.

690
00:39:17.020 --> 00:39:19.730
Train "B" is leaving your house...

691
00:39:20.770 --> 00:39:22.770
In 30 minutes.

692
00:39:22.860 --> 00:39:25.190
Thirty minutes seems like
an awfully long time

693
00:39:25.270 --> 00:39:27.110
