694
00:39:29.150 --> 00:39:30.360
[chuckles]

695
00:39:31.240 --> 00:39:33.450
Eisenhower Park. Rocket slide.

696
00:39:35.620 --> 00:39:37.540
Oh. my God. [laughs]

697
00:39:39.710 --> 00:39:41.250
I know what you're all thinking.

698
00:39:41.920 --> 00:39:43.540
Hannah Baker is a slut.

699
00:39:45.500 --> 00:39:47.000
Oops. Did you catch that?

700
00:39:48.050 --> 00:39:49.970
I just said "Hannah Baker is."

701
00:39:51.180 --> 00:39:52.390
Can't say that anymore.

702
00:39:53.970 --> 00:39:55.680
[laughter]

703
00:39:58.680 --> 00:40:00.230
Just wait. I'm gonna get you.

704
00:40:00.310 --> 00:40:01.190
[shouts]

705
00:40:01.270 --> 00:40:03.900
[Hannah] I dreamed our first kiss
would take place in the park.

706
00:40:05.060 --> 00:40:06.190
I never told you that.

707
00:40:11.780 --> 00:40:14.370
The dream starts with me
at the top of the rocket...

708
00:40:14.990 --> 00:40:16.410
holding on to the steering wheel.

709
00:40:17.410 --> 00:40:18.830
It's still a playground rocket.

710
00:40:18.910 --> 00:40:21.960
but every time I turn the wheel
to the left or the right.

711
00:40:22.040 --> 00:40:24.330
the trees lift up
like they're taking flight.

712
00:40:28.710 --> 00:40:30.630
[both laughing]

713
00:40:31.130 --> 00:40:32.840
-How was that?
-That was pretty good.

714
00:40:32.930 --> 00:40:34.260
-Yeah. you liked it?
-Yeah.

715
00:40:34.340 --> 00:40:35.720
[Justin] All right. your turn.

716
00:40:35.800 --> 00:40:36.640
-[Hannah] My turn?
-Yeah.

717
00:40:36.720 --> 00:40:39.100
Okay. What are you doing?

718
00:40:39.180 --> 00:40:41.060
Wait. wait. wait. wait.
I have to get this.

719
00:40:41.140 --> 00:40:43.770
-I'm wearing a skirt. Hang on. hang on.
-[mocking] I'm wearing a skirt!

720
00:40:43.850 --> 00:40:45.020
I got this. Let me just...

721
00:40:45.100 --> 00:40:48.570
And I'm scared...
because I don't know how to fly.

722
00:40:49.650 --> 00:40:52.780
But you're there at the bottom
of the slide to catch me when I fall.

723
00:40:53.360 --> 00:40:55.910
Okay. okay. One. two. three.

724
00:40:55.990 --> 00:40:58.530
-Ah! [giggles]
-[phone camera clicks]

725
00:40:59.160 --> 00:41:00.370
-You good?
-Yeah.

726
00:41:02.870 --> 00:41:04.370
And that's all that happened.

727
00:41:05.460 --> 00:41:06.290
We kissed.

728
00:41:16.220 --> 00:41:17.050
Why?

729
00:41:18.390 --> 00:41:19.810
Did you hear something else?

730
00:41:36.570 --> 00:41:38.700
[heavy breathing]

731
00:41:41.910 --> 00:41:42.830
Nope.

732
00:41:43.160 --> 00:41:44.500
We just kissed.

733
00:41:45.830 --> 00:41:50.420
Sorry to disappoint you.
but I guess now we're even. Sort of.

734
00:41:50.500 --> 00:41:52.170
[car approaching]

735
00:41:54.590 --> 00:41:57.260
-[engine shuts off]
-[car door opens. shuts]

736
00:42:05.810 --> 00:42:06.640
Hey. Clay.

737
00:42:07.810 --> 00:42:09.230
Hey. Tony.

738
00:42:10.230 --> 00:42:11.190
You okay?

739
00:42:12.320 --> 00:42:13.400
Yeah. fine.

740
00:42:16.400 --> 00:42:17.400
Is that my Walkman?

741
00:42:19.780 --> 00:42:20.700
Uh...

742
00:42:22.790 --> 00:42:24.120
Yeah. I was gonna ask--

743
00:42:24.200 --> 00:42:25.500
It's no sweat.

744
00:42:26.210 --> 00:42:28.330
Just be careful listening
while you ride. though.

745
00:42:28.830 --> 00:42:31.250
You don't want to hurt yourself. Again.

746
00:42:32.840 --> 00:42:34.710
You're right. Thanks.

747
00:42:37.340 --> 00:42:38.630
Eisenhower Park.

748
00:42:40.840 --> 00:42:43.180
That must mean you're about ready
for side two.

749
00:42:45.810 --> 00:42:48.270
Night. Clay. Take care of yourself.

750
00:42:55.070 --> 00:42:57.490
[Hannah] See. I've heard so many stories
about me now

751
00:42:57.570 --> 00:42:59.990
that I don't know which one
is the most popular.

752
00:43:01.240 --> 00:43:03.490
But I do know which is the least popular.

753
00:43:06.080 --> 00:43:07.080
The truth.

754
00:43:09.670 --> 00:43:13.040
See. the truth isn't always
the most exciting version of things.

755
00:43:13.130 --> 00:43:14.750
or the best or the worst.

756
00:43:15.670 --> 00:43:17.090
It's somewhere in between.

757
00:43:18.420 --> 00:43:20.630
But it deserves to be heard
and remembered.

758
00:43:23.050 --> 00:43:25.600
The truth will out.
like someone said once.

759
00:43:27.060 --> 00:43:28.140
It remains.

760
00:43:30.020 --> 00:43:31.190
[sighs]

761
00:43:42.990 --> 00:43:43.990
[button clicks]

762
00:43:44.910 --> 00:43:47.700
-[mellow music plays]
-So. thank you. Justin.

763
00:43:48.330 --> 00:43:52.000
Sincerely. My very first kiss
was wonderful.

764
00:44:17.230 --> 00:44:18.940
Porter wants to see me about Hannah.

765
00:44:19.780 --> 00:44:21.530
Probably about this fucking lawsuit.

766
00:44:27.240 --> 00:44:29.240
Did you get to first base. Justin?

767
00:44:29.330 --> 00:44:31.080
Get off me. I'm not saying anything.

768
00:44:31.160 --> 00:44:32.670
-Second?
-Fuck off.

769
00:44:33.960 --> 00:44:34.790
Third?

770
00:44:35.330 --> 00:44:36.500
Okay. assholes.

771
00:44:36.840 --> 00:44:39.920
-A picture's worth a thousand words.
-[chuckling]

772
00:44:40.010 --> 00:44:41.840
Public space.

773
00:44:43.130 --> 00:44:44.430
That's hot.

774
00:44:46.050 --> 00:44:47.680
Oh. yeah. We're sending that shit around.

775
00:44:47.760 --> 00:44:49.770
No. Bryce. stop!

776
00:44:49.850 --> 00:44:52.770
-[laughs]
-Hey. Bryce. stop! Hey!

777
00:44:52.850 --> 00:44:54.440
Bryce. come on. man!

778
00:44:54.520 --> 00:44:56.520
[boys laughing. chattering]

779
00:44:59.570 --> 00:45:01.650
[bell rings]

780
00:45:09.830 --> 00:45:11.660
-You gonna hit that again. right?
-Sure.

781
00:45:11.750 --> 00:45:14.250
